Hah. MEXICO, Playa Vicente (type), Santecomapam (vars, A and B) (Sella).

Front finely and subremotely punctured. Antennae with the second joint short, subtrigo- nate ; the third joint rather longer than the second, trigonate, its apex obliquely truncate, the inner and upper angle acute. Thorax scarcely broader than long; sides straight and parallel, the anterior angle very slightly produced, rounded; disc smooth and shining, impunctate ; on the anterior margin is a small ill-defined transverse nigro-piceous patch. Elytra parallel, flattened along the disc, very minutely punctate-striate3 each elytron with a broad fulvous vitta which commences at the base and extends downwards nearly to the apex. Medial portion of the apical margin of the abdominal segments more or less broadly edged with nigro-piceous.

The pattern of the elytra in the typical form of this insect, of which 1 know only the male, is similar to that of 0. quadrilineata, but the emargination os theanal segment of the abdomen in the male of that species is entirely different; the nigro-piceous markings on the abdomen sometimes forma narrow vitta on the medial disc.
